classification.Genus: †LomalatachelysLapparent de Broin and de la Fuente 2001[1]

text.__SUMMARY__:
Lomalatachelys neuquina is an extinct genus and species of chelid turtle from Argentina. The specimen was found in the Loma de La Lata zone approximately 75 km from Nuequen City in north west Patagonia, Argentina.
